1
00:01:08,074 --> 00:01:12,133
So you're here to write a new book?

2
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:19,600
I think you should revise your old one first.

3
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:25,066
The one about the theory of how to start liking someone...

4
00:01:25,566 --> 00:01:27,200
How to calculate it?

5
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:34,966
How about I help you think of a new title?

6
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:39,333
Well, what should it be?

7
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,700
How about this...

8
00:01:42,966 --> 00:01:46,866
"How to overcome defeat

9
00:01:47,266 --> 00:01:49,133
from the start"?

10
00:01:53,566 --> 00:01:55,533
It sounds good,

11
00:01:55,966 --> 00:02:01,133
but unfortunately, I'm not very good at writing about the loser.

12
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:22,633
You said you were going to prove that theory you wrote about.

13
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:26,100
Or were you just saying that to sound good?

14
00:02:26,466 --> 00:02:29,900
I really want to prove it. I'm not joking.

15
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:32,933
It's not to win against anyone,

16
00:02:34,566 --> 00:02:36,933
but I don't want the love I once believed in

17
00:02:37,233 --> 00:02:39,600
to become a lie in my own eyes.

18
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,300
That's it.

19
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:49,700
In conclusion, you're afraid of feeling guilty

20
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,233
Why are you saying something like this

21
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:59,666
when you don't understand a single thing in the book?

22
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:01,266
Do you think I don't understand?

23
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:04,500
I read it four times and took notes.

24
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,033
I'm sure I remember every line.

25
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:10,200
Four times?

26
00:03:10,866 --> 00:03:13,966
Normally, people who disagree

27
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,466
would stop reading after the first time.

28
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,333
And...

29
00:03:23,033 --> 00:03:25,866
if it turns out your theory is wrong,

30
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:27,166
will you accept it?

31
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:29,533
If it's wrong,

32
00:03:30,866 --> 00:03:32,666
I'll rewrite it myself.

33
00:03:34,066 --> 00:03:35,533
Well, be careful then.

34
00:03:37,233 --> 00:03:41,300
When you're determined to prove that theory...

35
00:03:41,466 --> 00:03:43,700
you'll become the subject of the theory yourself.

36
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:45,833
Okay then,

37
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:52,300
I'll make you believe it's real.

38
00:03:52,866 --> 00:03:54,933
Go ahead, writer.

39
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:56,700
I'm waiting.

40
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,733
Well...

41
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,466
why do you choose to stay here?

42
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:50,433
Normally, you just stare at your computer screen all day.

43
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:53,500
Why can't I be here?

44
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:55,633
I paid for the package.

45
00:04:58,533 --> 00:05:00,733
I thought you'd be the type to just let your emotions run wild,

46
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:03,500
but it seems you're more considerate than I thought.

47
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:10,066
Sometimes, using reason keeps us safe.

48
00:05:10,066 --> 00:05:14,800
At least we know we're not going down the wrong path.

49
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:19,800
I'm not afraid of my own heart, but you're the one who's afraid

50
00:05:19,966 --> 00:05:23,800
that one day reasons won't be able to overcome your feelings, right?

51
00:06:11,766 --> 00:06:12,266
One.

52
00:06:12,666 --> 00:06:13,166
Two.

53
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:14,200
Three.

54
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,200
Four.

55
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:23,566
I saw you looking at me just now.

56
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,933
You're blocking my view.

57
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:30,533
No, you were looking at me.

58
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:45,333
One.

59
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,300
Two.

60
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:47,166
Three.

61
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,100
Four.

62
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:49,133
Five.

63
00:06:49,533 --> 00:06:50,033
Six.

64
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,000
Seven.

65
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:52,033
Eight.

66
00:06:55,533 --> 00:06:56,500
I'm sorry.

67
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,466
It's alright.

68
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:03,700
I'll consider it a statistical accident .

69
00:07:04,266 --> 00:07:05,700
An accident, huh?

70
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:08,066
Then you should be careful,

71
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:12,400
because it won't hurt us...

72
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:15,666
but it might make our hearts race instead.

73
00:07:29,566 --> 00:07:34,933
Just eight seconds of eye contact is enough for hearts to start remembering each other.

74
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:39,966
At that moment, I thought it was just a short time

75
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:43,866
but my heart remembered it much longer than I thought.

76
00:08:12,566 --> 00:08:16,133
Is it this quiet here every night?

77
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:17,533
It's nice, actually.

78
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:20,400
Yes, it is.

79
00:08:22,866 --> 00:08:25,800
But sometimes the silence

80
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:30,866
can make those who are alone even lonelier.

81
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:41,233
I never thought I'd see this side of you.

82
00:08:44,066 --> 00:08:48,066
There are some sides of me I don't easily show to others,

83
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:52,233
especially those who see everything in terms of equations.

84
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:59,766
I'm surprised to see this side of you.

85
00:09:03,966 --> 00:09:08,166
Maybe it's because tonight is so lonely that

86
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:13,466
I accidentally said something I didn't want to say.

87
00:09:14,566 --> 00:09:18,933
Maybe it's because someone was listening

88
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:22,033
and you felt more comfortable speaking up.

89
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:27,466
You speak as if you understood everything.

90
00:09:38,233 --> 00:09:39,533
You probably think that...

91
00:09:40,533 --> 00:09:45,400
people who read this have no right to criticize what they're reading, right?

92
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,566
I'm not saying they don't have the right

93
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,000
but...

94
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:56,666
it should come from genuine understanding,

95
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:58,933
not from prejudice.

96
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,100
You know,

97
00:10:04,466 --> 00:10:07,233
there's a theory that says

98
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:10,433
people tend to speak harshly

99
00:10:10,766 --> 00:10:14,700
to those they're afraid will know the truth in their hearts.

100
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,466
Afraid?

101
00:10:21,633 --> 00:10:24,833
I'm not afraid of anything that can be proven,

102
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,055
especially...

103
00:10:28,275 --> 00:10:29,560
your feelings.

